1
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:08,880
啊
Ah.

2
00:02:15,720 --> 00:02:16,660
来吧
Come on.

3
00:02:39,970 --> 00:02:40,860
看着我
Look at me.

4
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:48,800
他去哪里了
Where'd he get to?

5
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,060
他去哪里了
Where'd he get to?

6
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:00,900
我不知道
I don't know.

7
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:08,400
不
No!

8
00:03:19,020 --> 00:03:19,980
拿绳子来
Get the rope.

9
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:27,460
我们 向东前往印第安领地
We's... headin' east, towards Indian territory.

10
00:03:30,880 --> 00:03:33,120
他的状况不好
He's in a bad way.

11
00:03:37,020 --> 00:03:38,980
这就是你要说的全部吗
Is that everything you have to say on the matter?

12
00:03:39,140 --> 00:03:41,580
我发誓 我发誓
I swear. I swear!

13
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:43,830
你知道吗
You know what?

14
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:46,840
我相信你
I believe you.

15
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:49,220
喔 达根
Whoa. Duggan.

16
00:03:54,740 --> 00:03:55,480
喔
Whoa.

17
00:03:56,880 --> 00:03:57,740
什么鬼
The hell?

18
00:04:03,180 --> 00:04:05,200
你他妈是怎么知道
How the hell you figure this wound up

19
00:04:05,260 --> 00:04:06,980
这片草地里有这东西的
out here in the middle of these grassland?

20
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,120
这真不错
This will work out nice.

21
00:04:17,940 --> 00:04:19,260
放我走
Just cut me loose.

22
00:04:19,380 --> 00:04:21,780
你再也不会见到我 真的 放我走吧
You'll never see me again, honest. Just cut me loose.

23
00:04:21,840 --> 00:04:22,740
坐起来
Sit on up.

24
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:25,880
好吧 听着 我可以放了你
Well, you see, I would cut you loose,

25
00:04:25,940 --> 00:04:28,620
但这会违背我对正义的坚持
but that just violates my sense of what's right.

26
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:05,400
老 亨 利

27
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:16,780
很难分辨一个人是谁 是什么人
It can be hard to tell who and what a man is,

28
00:05:17,060 --> 00:05:19,720
他有足够能力可以说服你
he's got a mind to convince you otherwise.

29
00:05:21,540 --> 00:05:25,020
我的族人来自我出生的纽约
My people were from New York, where I was born.

30
00:05:26,260 --> 00:05:28,020
我三岁的时候
By the time I was three,

31
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:30,820
我们来到堪萨斯州科菲维尔
we'd made it to coffeyville, Kansas,

32
00:05:31,420 --> 00:05:34,800
然后是亚利桑那州和新墨西哥州
then down to Arizona, then new Mexico.

33
00:05:36,440 --> 00:05:39,080
我曾在墨西哥呆过一段时间
I was in Mexico proper for a time.

34
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:43,760
我做过很多种职业
I've tried my hand at many a vocation.

35
00:05:46,620 --> 00:05:48,960
有些职业的收入更低
Some more marginal than others.

36
00:05:57,160 --> 00:06:01,340
最后 我决定做一个农民
Finally, I settled on the life of a farmer.

37
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:04,080
这就是我
Which is what I am.

38
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:09,930
俄克拉荷马于1907年加入美国联邦 成为第46个州
俄克拉荷马准州 -1906

39
00:06:51,020 --> 00:06:53,800
我们要储备猪饲料
We got that hog, stock to feed,

40
00:06:53,890 --> 00:06:55,340
把地窖装满
and a root cellar to fill.

41
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:58,700
现在有拖拉机可以在很短时间做完这些
There's tractors can do this now in quarter the time.

42
00:06:58,760 --> 00:06:59,920
是这样吗
Is that right?

43
00:07:00,730 --> 00:07:01,860
我认为这里
And here I thought

44
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,960
怀亚特 种田是你的本份
farming was in your bones, Wyatt.

45
00:07:06,280 --> 00:07:09,220
这里对你来说是个养家的好地方
This would be a good place for you to raise a family of your own.

46
00:07:09,380 --> 00:07:11,400
我知道你妈妈会这么想的
I know your ma would have felt that way.

47
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:12,860
我不是她
I ain't her.

48
00:07:15,020 --> 00:07:16,000
或他
Or him.

49
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:18,760
“人以智慧建造房屋”
By wisdom is a house built,

50
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:22,000
出自《圣经·箴言》 第24章第3节

51
00:07:19,540 --> 00:07:22,000
“以聪明使它立得稳固”
and through understanding is it established.

52
00:07:22,640 --> 00:07:24,820
“藉知识把房间充满各样”
Through knowledge are its rooms filled

53
00:07:24,860 --> 00:07:26,820
“珍奇美丽的宝物”
with rare and beautiful treasures.

54
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:30,380
“那些一心朝圣的人是有福的”
And blessed are those hearts that are set on pilgrimage.

55
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:34,480
尽管我想留下来
Much as I'd like to stick around...

56
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:37,920
听你们互相引用圣经
Listen to y'all quote scripture at each other...

57
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:39,870
我要去打鸟了
I'm goin' bird huntin'.

58
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:43,120
谢谢你帮我 艾尔
Thanks for the help, al.

59
00:07:44,410 --> 00:07:46,180
很高兴来这里
It does me good to be here.

60
00:07:47,820 --> 00:07:51,540
不知何故 这里仍然让我觉得与玛丽有联系
Makes me feel like I'm still connected to Marie somehow.

61
00:07:52,850 --> 00:07:54,940
帮你舅父收拾一下东西
Give your uncle a hand with his things.

62
00:07:55,380 --> 00:07:57,920
前提是你已经休息好了
That is, if you've had sufficient respite.

63
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:18,540
谢谢你 孩子
Thank you, son.

64
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:20,260
好的 舅父
Yes, sir.

65
00:08:20,380 --> 00:08:22,260
我今天早上准备去打猎
Yeah, I wanted to go huntin' this mornin',

66
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:24,200
但你爸说他需要帮忙
but your pa said he needed some help.

67
00:08:25,100 --> 00:08:27,220
我当然想有一天和你一起去
Sure would like to go with you one of these days.

68
00:08:27,700 --> 00:08:29,920
我觉得这不太合适
I don't think that'd go over too well.

69
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:33,390
你爸是个好人 怀亚特
Your pa's a good man, Wyatt.

70
00:08:33,860 --> 00:08:36,960
否则我也不会让妹妹嫁给他了
I wouldn't let him marry my sister if I didn't think so.

71
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:41,000
用不了多久 你就可以
Soon enough, you'll be able to

72
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:44,420
随心所欲去旅行和打猎了
do all the travelin' and shootin' you want to.

73
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:47,400
别再纠结这个
Stop frettin' about it.

74
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:08,240
我们晚饭吃两块排骨 其余的熏制起来
We'll take two chops for supper and smoke the rest.

75
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:10,720
我没时间打理这些
I ain't got time to render this.

76
00:09:12,060 --> 00:09:13,320
扔到猪舍里
Throw it in the pen.

77
00:09:32,380 --> 00:09:34,560
你不觉得难受吗 它们吃自己
Don't it bother you sometimes, they eat their own?

78
00:09:35,540 --> 00:09:37,700
对猪来说没什么区别
Don't make no difference to a hog.

79
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:53,900
你为什么住在这里
Why'd you settle here?

80
00:09:54,700 --> 00:09:56,140
是什么意思
What's that meant to mean?

81
00:09:57,360 --> 00:10:01,520
为什么在准州 不是别的地方
Why? Why the territory, of all places?

82
00:10:03,180 --> 00:10:04,640
因为可以主张所有权
You could stake a claim,

83
00:10:03,180 --> 00:10:09,990
指1889年4月 俄克拉荷马准州发生的“圈地潮”

84
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:06,920
持续使用一年 它就是你的了
hang onto it for a year, it was yours.

85
00:10:07,720 --> 00:10:09,990
在当时似乎是个不错的交易
Seemed like a pretty good deal at the time.

86
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:15,180
你知道的 必须在枪响前赶到这里
Got here before the guns went off, you know that.

87
00:10:15,940 --> 00:10:18,030
我还是不信这就是你想要的
I still don't believe this is what you wanted.

88
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:23,530
黎明时分起床 喂牲口 收割庄稼
Up at dawn, feedin' the stock, workin' the crops.

89
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:26,440
无论热还是冷 雨或晴
Hot or cold, rain or shine.

90
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:29,060
你会发现有更糟糕的安排
You'll discover there's worse arrangements.

91
00:10:38,110 --> 00:10:38,920
爸爸
Pa?

92
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:22,220
放松 姑娘 就这样
Easy, gal, that's it.

93
00:11:24,490 --> 00:11:26,760
我在你这么大的时候
Had me a mare near just like this

94
00:11:26,820 --> 00:11:28,280
就像这样靠近过一匹母马
when I wasn't much older than you.

95
00:11:29,580 --> 00:11:30,480
看这里
Lookie here.

96
00:11:33,980 --> 00:11:36,580
你觉得发生了什么 是抢劫吗
What do you think happened? Some kind of robbery?

97
00:11:37,010 --> 00:11:39,110
-枪战 -别乱说
-A shootout? -Shut your nonsense.

98
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:42,400
我最好去找那个骑手
I'd best go look for the rider.

99
00:11:43,140 --> 00:11:44,320
好的 我去装马鞍
Yeah, I'll go saddle up.

100
00:11:45,020 --> 00:11:48,200
你看好这匹马 待在里面等我回来
You tend to this horse and stay inside till I get back.

101
00:11:48,860 --> 00:11:50,980
但如果有麻烦呢 爸爸 我可以帮你
But what if it's trouble, pa? I can help you.

102
00:11:51,060 --> 00:11:53,060
继续 照我说的做
Go on. Do as I say.

103
00:14:01,960 --> 00:14:02,860
喂
Hello.

104
00:15:56,020 --> 00:15:56,960
不好
Nope.

105
00:17:16,420 --> 00:17:17,310
怀亚特
Wyatt!

106
00:17:19,240 --> 00:17:21,060
-他还活着吗 -还有口气
-Is he alive? -Barely.

107
00:17:21,280 --> 00:17:22,480
他一个人吗
Was he alone?

108
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:28,040
是的 但那里还有其他人的踪迹
No, but I dispatched with a dozen others was there.

109
00:17:28,360 --> 00:17:29,300
帮我一把
Give me a hand.

110
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:32,040
他 他失血过多
He's... he's lost a lot of blood.

111
00:17:40,680 --> 00:17:41,760
他还能活吗
Is he gonna live?

112
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:44,080
我想取决于我们
Be up to us, I suppose.

113
00:17:44,140 --> 00:17:46,260
现在太晚路又远 没法去找医生
Too far and too late to fetch the doc.

114
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:50,540
我去 如果必要 可以连夜赶路
Well, I can go. Ride all night if I have to.

115
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:51,880
我相信你可以
I'm sure you would.

116
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:54,800
所以
So?

117
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:57,900
你就呆在这里 把那瓶金缕梅给我
You'll stay right here. Hand over that witch Hazel.

118
00:18:05,300 --> 00:18:06,540
他是个亡命徒
That is an outlaw.

119
00:18:07,280 --> 00:18:09,360
在奔跑中摔下了马
On the run, shot off his horse.

120
00:18:10,300 --> 00:18:11,580
你觉得他杀过人吗
You think he killed somebody?

121
00:18:11,740 --> 00:18:14,480
怀亚特 我知道的跟你一样多
Wyatt, I know just as much as you do.

122
00:18:15,460 --> 00:18:16,560
那是做什么
What's that for?

123
00:18:17,020 --> 00:18:19,940
把伤口扎紧 以免他夜里失血太多
Seal the wound tight so he don't bleed out overnight.

124
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:24,960
不 胸部受伤千万别抬高双脚
No! Don't never elevate the feet with a chest wound.

125
00:18:34,260 --> 00:18:35,900
我看到了你身上的伤疤
I've seen the scars on your body.

126
00:18:36,280 --> 00:18:37,940
因为我没有对你隐瞒
'Cause I ain't hid'em from you.

127
00:18:38,930 --> 00:18:41,240
现在也许你明白你的成长经历了
Now maybe you'll understand your raisin'.

128
00:18:41,660 --> 00:18:43,030
来压住这里
Put your hand right here.

129
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:49,840
你要去哪里
Where you goin'?

130
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:52,220
在我回来前一直压着
Just keep applyin' pressure till I get back.

131
00:21:40,940 --> 00:21:41,860
现在做什么
What now?

132
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:45,500
子弹必须出来 不然他会死
Bullet's gotta come out. And he won't make the ride.

133
00:21:47,100 --> 00:21:48,260
分开绳子
Half that rope.

134
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,480
我去找医生
I'll fetch the doc.

135
00:22:03,900 --> 00:22:05,940
你留在这里看着他
You'll stay here and keep an eye on him.

136
00:22:13,320 --> 00:22:15,120
你真的觉得有必要吗
You really think that's necessary?

137
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:17,110
有必要
It ain't not necessary.

138
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:20,150
你为什么不冷静下来
Now, why don't you cool his fever

139
00:22:20,180 --> 00:22:21,740
而不是为你
instead of vaporizin' on every

140
00:22:21,780 --> 00:22:23,550
脑子里的想法感到自豪
thought that comes into your head?

141
00:22:53,940 --> 00:22:55,020
没有痕迹
Trail's cold.

142
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:00,520
我们会抓住他
We'll get him.

143
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:32,220
那家伙能在水中追踪鱼
That dog could track a fish through water.

144
00:23:35,960 --> 00:23:36,780
走吧
Come on.

145
00:23:47,100 --> 00:23:49,260
如果他醒了 你要保持距离
He should come to, you keep your distance.

146
00:23:49,280 --> 00:23:50,910
没事 他被绑住了
It don't matter he's tied up.

147
00:23:51,240 --> 00:23:52,640
我自己能处理
I can handle myself.

148
00:23:52,670 --> 00:23:55,180
照我说的做 我会尽快回来
You just do as I say. I'll be back soon as I can.

149
00:23:55,210 --> 00:23:56,060
走吧
Come on.

150
00:26:58,380 --> 00:26:59,520
比利在哪里
Where's Billy at?

151
00:27:04,220 --> 00:27:06,200
是谁

152
00:27:10,540 --> 00:27:13,180
低下头 你会没事的
Keep your head down. You'll be all right.

153
00:28:25,350 --> 00:28:26,220
哇
Whoa.

154
00:29:38,120 --> 00:29:39,160
他来过这里
He was here.

155
00:29:42,100 --> 00:29:43,540
我不这么认为
Don't look like it to me.

156
00:29:52,660 --> 00:29:55,340
如果我没猜错 他不是一个人
If I'm right, he weren't alone.

157
00:29:59,980 --> 00:30:01,740
不管是谁都知道他做了什么
Whoever it is knows what he's doin'.

158
00:30:05,620 --> 00:30:08,220
他像其他人一样很好的掩盖了行踪
Covered his tracks as good as anyone I've run across.

159
00:30:09,460 --> 00:30:11,480
要不是这场雨 我早就找到他了
Weren't for this rain, I'd have found him sooner.

160
00:30:12,220 --> 00:30:14,740
我不需要听你那愚蠢的
I don't need you to speechify the inner workings

161
00:30:14,800 --> 00:30:17,090
狗脑子是如何推测的
in your halfwit canine mind.

162
00:30:18,330 --> 00:30:19,860
我只想知道他在哪里
I need to know where he's headed.

163
00:30:25,100 --> 00:30:27,340
嗯 这并不能缩小搜索范围
Well, that don't exactly narrow it down.

164
00:32:16,660 --> 00:32:18,000
我在哪里
Where am I?

165
00:32:24,500 --> 00:32:25,600
你到底是谁
Who the hell are you?

166
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:29,500
我爸爸发现你 快死了
M-My pa found you, close to dead.

167
00:32:29,660 --> 00:32:30,800
他把你带回来了
He brought you back here.

168
00:32:31,060 --> 00:32:32,060
噢 是吗
Oh, yeah?

169
00:32:32,480 --> 00:32:33,580
你爸爸是谁
Who's your pa?

170
00:32:34,220 --> 00:32:35,280
普通人 呃
Nobody. Uh...

171
00:32:35,820 --> 00:32:37,580
亨利 就是个农民
Henry. Just a-a farmer.

172
00:32:50,440 --> 00:32:52,160
什么 这里只有你和他
What, it's only you and him here?

173
00:32:55,220 --> 00:32:56,400
他现在在吗
He here now?

174
00:32:59,740 --> 00:33:00,980
他就在后面
He's just out back.

175
00:33:03,420 --> 00:33:04,680
在喂猪
Tendin' to the hogs.

176
00:33:07,060 --> 00:33:08,060
噢 是吗
Oh, yeah?

177
00:33:12,660 --> 00:33:13,840
好吧 去叫他来
Well, go fetch him.

178
00:33:27,860 --> 00:33:29,680
不要 动
Quit mov... moving!

179
00:33:31,220 --> 00:33:32,440
好了 我不想伤害你
Right now, I don't want to hurt you.

180
00:33:32,540 --> 00:33:34,300
我不想伤害你 别动
I don't want to hurt you. Stop moving!

181
00:33:34,390 --> 00:33:36,460
你把我的枪和包放哪儿了 听我说
Where'd you put my gun and my satchel? Listen to me!

182
00:33:37,040 --> 00:33:38,800
我不知道你在说什么 先生
I don't know what you're talkin' about, mister.

183
00:33:38,820 --> 00:33:39,820
别骗我
Don't you lie to me!

184
00:33:39,980 --> 00:33:42,120
你拿我的枪和包做什么
What'd you do with my gun and my satchel?

185
00:34:10,360 --> 00:34:11,280
爸爸
Pa!

186
00:34:15,260 --> 00:34:16,600
他是怎么逃脱的
How'd he get loose?

187
00:34:17,530 --> 00:34:18,780
他扭动着挣脱了
H-He wriggled free.

188
00:34:19,360 --> 00:34:20,500
挣脱的
Wriggled free?

189
00:34:21,380 --> 00:34:24,040
他拿到我留在床头柜上的刀了
And got hold of my knife I left on the bedstand.

190
00:34:25,040 --> 00:34:26,780
我们两个都有责任
Well, that's on the both of us.

191
00:34:28,120 --> 00:34:30,480
帮我把这混蛋绑起来
Help me tie the son of a bitch back up.

192
00:34:59,960 --> 00:35:00,910
好吧
Okay.

193
00:35:02,980 --> 00:35:05,380
你最好仔细想想你自己惹的麻烦
You better think long and hard on what you got yourself into.

194
00:35:06,040 --> 00:35:08,650
有趣 我正要对你说同样的话
Funny, I was about to tell you the same thing.

195
00:35:11,390 --> 00:35:12,920
你想拿它做什么
What you aimin' to do with that?

196
00:35:14,180 --> 00:35:16,180
把你身上的子弹取出来
Gonna dig that bullet out of you,

197
00:35:16,580 --> 00:35:18,860
也许在这过程中会得到些答案
maybe get some answers in the process.

198
00:35:19,340 --> 00:35:20,820
听到我想听的
I like what I hear,

199
00:35:21,240 --> 00:35:24,240
我也许会给你点减轻痛苦的东西
I might be inclined to give you something to ease the pain.

200
00:35:30,100 --> 00:35:30,940
不
No.

201
00:35:34,240 --> 00:35:35,160
不
No!

202
00:35:35,860 --> 00:35:37,780
好吧 听着 听着
Okay! Listen, listen!

203
00:35:38,440 --> 00:35:39,450
不
No!

204
00:35:39,480 --> 00:35:41,960
从你告诉我你是谁开始
Let's start with you tellin' me who you are.

205
00:35:42,200 --> 00:35:44,340
我是执法人员 是个警察
I'm law! I'm a goddamn lawman!

206
00:35:45,600 --> 00:35:48,320
他不是警察 爸爸 他想杀了我
He ain't no lawman, pa, he was fixin' to kill me.

207
00:35:48,600 --> 00:35:50,100
想喝点威士忌吗
Ready for some whisky?

208
00:35:50,300 --> 00:35:52,460
我说了 我是执法人员
I just told you... I'm law.

209
00:35:54,700 --> 00:35:55,920
问他钱的事
Ask him about the money.

210
00:35:57,570 --> 00:35:58,500
什么钱
What money?

211
00:35:59,300 --> 00:36:00,700
他问过我这个
He asked me about it.

212
00:36:02,080 --> 00:36:03,720
听着 听我说
Listen. Listen to me.

213
00:36:03,800 --> 00:36:04,810
好把 听着
Okay, listen.

214
00:36:05,040 --> 00:36:08,000
一个拿着满满一包现金的警察在干什么
What's a shot lawman doin' with a satchel full of cash?

215
00:36:08,040 --> 00:36:08,860
听着
Listen!

216
00:36:09,620 --> 00:36:11,740
听着 如果你还有脑子
Listen! If you got a brain in your head,

217
00:36:11,920 --> 00:36:13,640
你就必须带上你的孩子
you need to get yourself and your boy

218
00:36:13,680 --> 00:36:15,120
尽快离开这里
out of here fast as you can.

219
00:36:15,420 --> 00:36:16,340
听到了吗
You hear me?

220
00:36:21,900 --> 00:36:22,740
不
No.

221
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:24,720
噢 不 不 不
Oh, no! No, no!

222
00:36:40,720 --> 00:36:42,180
至少在我找到想知道的之前
At least we know you won't die

223
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:44,300
你一时还死不了
'fore I find out what I want to know.

224
00:36:51,820 --> 00:36:52,760
噢 上帝
Oh god.

225
00:36:55,820 --> 00:36:57,580
给我再喝点
Let me have a little more.

226
00:36:58,000 --> 00:36:58,900
让我
Let me...

227
00:37:04,020 --> 00:37:04,920
有骑手
Riders.

228
00:37:09,540 --> 00:37:12,570
拜托 放开我 快 放开我
Come on, cut me loose. Come on, cut me loose.

229
00:37:14,940 --> 00:37:16,880
听着 他们可能有三个人
Listen, they gon' be three of'em.

230
00:37:18,510 --> 00:37:19,840
一个是墨西哥人
One's a Mexican.

231
00:37:21,300 --> 00:37:23,500
另一个是留着大胡子的
The other's an ugly son of a bitch

232
00:37:23,840 --> 00:37:25,000
丑八怪
with a thick beard.

233
00:37:25,700 --> 00:37:26,790
而他们的头
And their leader...

234
00:37:27,320 --> 00:37:29,760
他们的老大看起来是个你不想惹的人
Their leader looks like a man you don't want to mess with.

235
00:37:30,190 --> 00:37:32,220
相信我 你不会想惹
And believe me, you don't.

236
00:37:32,660 --> 00:37:34,030
不要靠近窗户
Keep back from the window.

237
00:37:35,340 --> 00:37:37,600
如果你们想活命 就放开我
If you want to live, you gotta turn me loose

238
00:37:37,620 --> 00:37:38,820
把枪给我 听到了吗
and give me my gun, hear?

239
00:37:39,780 --> 00:37:40,770
他在撒谎
He's lyin'.

240
00:37:40,800 --> 00:37:42,200
我说了退后
I said keep back.

241
00:37:42,840 --> 00:37:43,760
照做
Go on.

242
00:38:38,680 --> 00:38:39,720
我能帮你们吗
Can I help you?

243
00:38:40,740 --> 00:38:42,280
我是萨姆·凯彻姆警长
I'm sheriff Sam ketchum.

244
00:38:42,480 --> 00:38:43,900
他们是我的副手
These here are my deputies.

245
00:38:44,900 --> 00:38:47,000
我们一直在追踪一个逃犯
We've been scoutin' for a man on the run.

246
00:38:47,380 --> 00:38:49,300
他最近自称叫柯里
Lately goes by the name of curry.

247
00:38:50,540 --> 00:38:51,520
被击伤了
Been shot.

248
00:38:52,560 --> 00:38:55,700
六英尺高 棕色头发 据说很帅
Six foot, brown hair, said to be handsome,

249
00:38:56,420 --> 00:38:59,140
尽管大多数人都觉得他只是个小混混
though most would want him credited for nothing but devilry.

250
00:39:01,360 --> 00:39:04,140
但我知道 他很危险
What I do know is, he's dangerous.

251
00:39:05,220 --> 00:39:07,760
你看到这附近有这些特征的人吗
You seen anybody around here answers that description?

252
00:39:08,560 --> 00:39:12,130
你说你是警长 我怎么不认识你
Say you're a sheriff? How's it I don't recognize you?

253
00:39:12,760 --> 00:39:14,700
我们从伍兹县那边来的
We're from way over in woods county.

254
00:39:15,860 --> 00:39:17,140
我们现在要找的柯里
Now, this curry we're looking for,

255
00:39:17,160 --> 00:39:18,630
他在密苏里州和
he's got a warrant on him there

256
00:39:18,940 --> 00:39:20,900
田纳西州都有逮捕令
in Missouri and Tennessee.

257
00:39:21,880 --> 00:39:23,760
他可能自称是执法人员
Might also claim he's the law.

258
00:39:24,740 --> 00:39:26,780
他曾经玩过这种把戏
He's got a history of such chicanery.

259
00:39:27,640 --> 00:39:28,660
但远非如此
Far from it.

260
00:39:29,520 --> 00:39:30,560
他是个杀手
He's a killer.

261
00:39:31,100 --> 00:39:32,480
他会再次杀人
He will kill again.

262
00:39:35,150 --> 00:39:36,250
你不会用那把枪
You're not fixin' to shoot

263
00:39:36,280 --> 00:39:37,800
朝我们射击吧 是吗
any of us with that pistol, are you?

264
00:39:39,660 --> 00:39:41,790
目前我没理由这么做
So far I got no reason to.

265
00:39:43,060 --> 00:39:44,130
是个好消息
That's good news.

266
00:39:47,380 --> 00:39:50,500
农夫 在你举起那把枪前得想清楚
You'll want to think'fore you raise that thing up, farmer.

267
00:39:52,320 --> 00:39:54,320
没什么好担心的 朋友
Nothing to be worried about here, friend.

268
00:39:54,700 --> 00:39:56,380
只是我正在做的一个小东西
Just a little project I'm working on,

269
00:39:56,700 --> 00:39:57,580
仅此而已
that's all.

270
00:39:59,480 --> 00:40:01,180
有多少人住在这里
How many people live out here?

271
00:40:02,860 --> 00:40:04,420
这和你有什么关系
What difference is that to you?

272
00:40:04,540 --> 00:40:06,800
我只是想确定你是安全的
I'm trying to make sure you're safe, is all.

273
00:40:07,620 --> 00:40:09,160
这似乎不归你管
Wouldn't seem to be your business,

274
00:40:09,200 --> 00:40:11,400
因为你是从伍兹县来的
seeing as how you're from woods county.

275
00:40:12,920 --> 00:40:13,860
你结过婚
You married?

276
00:40:14,980 --> 00:40:16,560
我看见那边有一座坟墓
Saw a grave over there.

277
00:40:19,140 --> 00:40:20,060
是我妻子
My wife.

278
00:40:21,100 --> 00:40:23,820
十年前死于肺结核
Died ten years back from tuberculosis.

279
00:40:26,100 --> 00:40:27,180
节哀顺变
My condolences.

280
00:40:29,670 --> 00:40:31,000
可怕的离开方式
Horrible way to go.

281
00:40:31,880 --> 00:40:33,920
爸爸 告诉他们
Tell'em, pa. Tell'em!

282
00:40:33,980 --> 00:40:36,300
墓上刻着 玛丽·霍布斯·麦卡蒂
Marie hobbs mccarty, the marker said.

283
00:40:37,300 --> 00:40:38,660
你姓麦卡蒂
Your last name mccarty?

284
00:40:39,180 --> 00:40:40,110
没错
That's right.

285
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:42,320
名字呢
First name?

286
00:40:46,350 --> 00:40:47,240
亨利
Henry.

287
00:40:49,940 --> 00:40:51,930
我猜霍布斯是她的族人
So hobbs was her people, I'm guessing.

288
00:40:52,540 --> 00:40:54,860
因为我看到东边有个霍布斯农场
'Cause I noticed a hobbs ranch to the east of here.

289
00:40:55,460 --> 00:40:56,600
是她的兄弟
Her brothers.

290
00:40:57,460 --> 00:40:58,300
嗯
Uh-huh.

291
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:02,200
嗯 从这些东西来看
Well, from the looks of things,

292
00:41:02,270 --> 00:41:04,010
你在这里已经住了多年
you've been out here a good many years.

293
00:41:06,340 --> 00:41:07,560
环境不错
Nice situation.

294
00:41:08,500 --> 00:41:10,380
都依偎在这群山中
All nestled up here in the hills.

295
00:41:10,680 --> 00:41:12,210
从远处很难发现
Hard to see from a distance.

296
00:41:13,600 --> 00:41:16,650
这跟你要找的那个人有什么关系
What's any of this got to do with the man you're lookin' for?

297
00:41:17,700 --> 00:41:19,150
关系不大 我承认
Not much, I'll Grant you.

298
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:24,000
很久以前 呃
Long time ago, uh...

299
00:41:24,480 --> 00:41:28,940
一个人在新墨西哥州和亚利桑那州惹了些麻烦
Was a fella caused some trouble down Arizona, new Mexico way.

300
00:41:30,030 --> 00:41:31,760
听说他叫麦卡蒂
Heard he went by the name mccarty.

301
00:41:33,930 --> 00:41:35,840
我想知道他是否是你的亲戚
I was wondering if he might be your kin.

302
00:41:37,140 --> 00:41:39,420
你找错人了
You got the wrong pig by the ear.

303
00:41:40,040 --> 00:41:40,920
意思是
Meaning?

304
00:41:41,040 --> 00:41:44,810
除了这里 我不认识任何地方的麦卡蒂
I don't know no mccartys anywhere but here,

305
00:41:44,850 --> 00:41:46,910
我所有亲戚都死了
and all my kin is deceased.

306
00:41:48,640 --> 00:41:50,660
现在我要做晚饭
Now I got chores to tend to

307
00:41:50,700 --> 00:41:52,660
木柴不够 我要干活去了
and scant wood to cook my supper.

308
00:41:53,860 --> 00:41:55,980
我没见过你要找的人
I ain't seen the man you're after.

309
00:41:56,420 --> 00:41:58,030
我会保持警惕
I'll keep my eyes peeled.

310
00:41:58,700 --> 00:42:00,700
如果我在切克沙见到他
Be sure to alert the good sheriff

311
00:42:00,730 --> 00:42:02,930
肯定会通知好警长
in chickasha if I should run across him.

312
00:42:06,300 --> 00:42:07,220
那好吧
Well, then.

313
00:42:08,740 --> 00:42:09,880
谢谢你的帮助
I thank you for your help.

314
00:42:12,480 --> 00:42:14,500
看起来又是条死胡同 孩子们
Looks like another dead end, boys.

315
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:18,950
你今晚一定要关好门
You be sure to lock your doors tonight.

316
00:42:21,860 --> 00:42:22,840
注意安全
Stay safe.

317
00:42:26,820 --> 00:42:27,680
走吧
Come on.

318
00:42:50,020 --> 00:42:51,900
现在你想用这个了吗
Now you're inclined to hang onto that?

319
00:42:51,940 --> 00:42:53,120
我想你可能需要帮助
I thought you might be needin' help.

320
00:42:53,160 --> 00:42:54,920
你想告诉我这是怎么用的吗
You wanna tell me how this got fired?

321
00:42:55,740 --> 00:42:56,960
我会用 爸爸
Honest, pa.

322
00:42:57,060 --> 00:42:58,240
别骗我
Don't you lie to me!

323
00:42:59,560 --> 00:43:01,440
我知道它如何使用
I wanted to know what it's like.

324
00:43:02,200 --> 00:43:06,580
我是50英里内唯一一个从未开过枪的男孩
I am the only boy for 50 miles that's never fired one.

325
00:43:06,940 --> 00:43:09,400
你甚至不让我碰你的旧猎枪
You won't even let me lay hand on your old shotgun.

326
00:43:09,430 --> 00:43:13,040
所以你不教我射击 我只能自己学
So if you can't teach me proper, I gotta do it myself.

327
00:43:13,130 --> 00:43:17,470
如果你再动我的枪 我就揍你
You get into my things again, I will crack your crust!

328
00:43:19,280 --> 00:43:22,420
你就是个又蠢又没用的老头
You're a stupid, worthless old man.

329
00:43:22,960 --> 00:43:25,360
一辈子除了守着这破农场
A whole life, and nothin' to show for it

330
00:43:25,420 --> 00:43:26,880
根本碌碌无为
but this rundown old farm

331
00:43:26,910 --> 00:43:30,380
还有一个会离开你 让你孤独老死的男孩
and a boy who's gonna leave you alone to die as soon as he's able.

332
00:43:43,430 --> 00:43:44,520
让我猜猜
Let me guess.

333
00:43:45,230 --> 00:43:48,740
你会告诉我他不是伍兹县的治安官
You gon' tell me that he ain't the sheriff of woods county, you are.

334
00:43:49,200 --> 00:43:51,200
他们不是 他们是银行劫匪
They ain't lawmen, they're bank robbers.

335
00:43:51,700 --> 00:43:53,740
好吧 他们干了些什么
Well, what's left of them, anyway.

336
00:43:55,910 --> 00:43:57,680
抢劫了亚当斯快车
Knocked over the Adams express.

337
00:43:59,110 --> 00:44:01,240
我和副手追上去杀了其中两人
Me and my deputies gave chase, killed two of'em,

338
00:44:01,340 --> 00:44:02,640
包括那个携带赃款的人
including the one carrying the loot.

339
00:44:02,680 --> 00:44:04,520
银行劫匪戴着徽章
Bank robbers wearin' badges?

340
00:44:04,620 --> 00:44:06,190
他们从我们这里偷的
That they took off me and my men.

341
00:44:07,190 --> 00:44:08,900
他是冒充执法人员
He's the one impersonating the law.

342
00:44:10,680 --> 00:44:12,340
但是你把钱拿走了
But you made off with the money.

343
00:44:14,200 --> 00:44:15,460
见鬼 是的 我拿了
Hell, yeah, I grabbed it.

344
00:44:17,200 --> 00:44:19,680
那你为什么不带着钱回伍兹县
Then why ain't you back with it in woods county?

345
00:44:20,470 --> 00:44:24,100
噢 不知道 为什么必须这么做
Oh, I don't know. Why does it look like?

346
00:44:27,210 --> 00:44:28,280
我的首要任务是
And my first priority was

347
00:44:28,310 --> 00:44:29,900
活着逃离那伙人
getting away from that bunch alive.

348
00:44:30,000 --> 00:44:32,020
这就是为什么我拼命跑 直到晕倒
That's why I rode like hell till I couldn't no more.

349
00:44:32,680 --> 00:44:34,880
我记得的最后一件事 就是在这里醒来
There's the last thing I remembered, till I woke up here.

350
00:44:37,450 --> 00:44:39,940
听着 我知道这些话对你来说都很荒谬
Look, I know what I'm saying sounds ridiculous to you and all.

351
00:44:40,180 --> 00:44:41,360
确实如此
That it does.

352
00:44:41,440 --> 00:44:44,060
我不知道他们刚才为什么没开枪杀了你
Why they didn't shoot you dead on the spot just now, I don't know.

353
00:44:45,660 --> 00:44:46,760
但我可以向你保证
But I can guarantee you...

354
00:44:48,380 --> 00:44:49,340
他们会回来的
They'll be back.

355
00:45:44,240 --> 00:45:46,020
我唯一不明白是
Only thing I can't figure

356
00:45:46,240 --> 00:45:49,220
那老头为什么会为一个陌生人冒生命危险
is why the old man would risk his neck for a stranger.

357
00:45:50,160 --> 00:45:52,230
也许他得到了一笔钱
Maybe he got offered a cut of the money.

358
00:45:53,630 --> 00:45:55,360
有些迹象表明不是这样
Something tells me that ain't it.

359
00:45:57,580 --> 00:45:59,500
我们谁都可以干掉他
Any one of us could have taken him out.

360
00:46:00,400 --> 00:46:01,900
这就是我们现在该做的
Which is what we should do now.

361
00:46:02,540 --> 00:46:06,110
-马上行动 -还不行
-Ride up, finish it. -Not just yet.

362
00:46:09,440 --> 00:46:11,540
因为那个东倒西歪的老农
'Cause of some shaky old farmer?

363
00:46:12,040 --> 00:46:15,280
他不像我见过的任何农民那样拿枪
He didn't hold that pistol like any farmer I've ever seen.

364
00:46:16,360 --> 00:46:17,660
我们有三个人
There are three of us.

365
00:46:19,140 --> 00:46:22,390
我们不会抢银行 也不会不了解情况
We don't run up in a bank, or ride up on a stage

366
00:46:22,420 --> 00:46:23,680
就去抢劫驿站
without knowing who's in it.

367
00:46:24,460 --> 00:46:27,260
但我们知道柯里带着钱在房子里
We know curry's in there. With our money!

368
00:46:27,380 --> 00:46:31,120
这就是你要去侦察那个所谓农夫之家的原因
Which is why you're going to reconnoiter that so-called farmer's place

369
00:46:31,600 --> 00:46:33,440
确保柯里还没有逃走
and make sure curry don't skedaddle.

370
00:46:34,360 --> 00:46:35,320
很乐意
Gladly.

371
00:46:37,120 --> 00:46:39,000
在我们到之前不要妄动
Don't make a move till we get there.

372
00:46:40,420 --> 00:46:41,320
好的
Fine.

373
00:46:42,900 --> 00:46:44,820
-达根 -我说很好
-Duggan. -I said fine.

